{{Infobox Union |name= CGTL |country= [[Lebanon]] |affiliation= |members= 200,000 |full_name= General Confederation of Lebanese Workers |native_name= Confédération Générale des Travailleurs du Liban |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= |predecessor= [[Antoine Bechara]] |people= [[Ghassan Ghosn]], president |website= |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''General Confederation of Lebanese Workers''' (CGTL) (in [[French language|French]] Confédération Générale des Travailleurs Libanais (CGTL), in [[Arabic language|Arabic]] الإتحاد العمالي العام في لبنان) is a liberal [[national trade union center]] in [[Lebanon]]. It was founded in 1958, and has a membership of 200,000. The original president of the confederation, Antoine Bechara, was president from 1983 to 1991 and created its logo.
