The '''Korean Labor Unions Confederation''' (KLUC), also known as '''Gukmin<small>-</small>nochong''' ({{lang-ko|국민노총}}; acronym for ''KLUC'' in Korean language) was a [[national trade union centre]] of [[South Korea]] established in 2011, and the union merged into [[Federation of Korean Trade Unions]] in 2014.
