{{Infobox company | name = Palink, UAB | native_name = | native_name_lang = | trading_name = IKI | logo = Iki.png | logo_size = 150px | logo_caption = Iki logo | image = IKI Express in Vilnius.jpg | image_caption = IKI Express shop in Vilnius downtown | predecessor = | successor = | founder = George Ortiz, Nicolas Ortiz, Oliver Ortiz | area_served = Lithuania | key_people =CEO Gerard Rog (2015 07-) | industry = Retail | revenue = [[Euro|€]]0.632 billion <ref name= vz>[https://www.vz.lt/verslo-aplinka/top1000-2017]</ref> (2016) | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | foundation = {{Start date|1992}} | location_city = [[Vilnius]] | location_country = [[Lithuania]] | homepage = {{URL|www.iki.lt}} }} '''Palink''' is the operator of the "IKI" supermarket chain in Lithuania.
== History == Palink was founded by the brothers George, Oliver and Nicolas Ortiz.<ref>https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB108310342029695152</ref> The first store was opened in 1992 in [[Vilnius]], Lithuania.
In 2005 Palink opened its first store in [[Riga]], Latvia.
In 2014 Palink sold all IKI stores in Latvia (51 stores) to local company "Mego", stating that Palink is not interested in investing in Latvia anymore. IKI was 5th largest supermarket chain in Latvia.<ref>[http://vz.lt/article/2014/1/17/palink-parduoda-parduotuviu-tinkla-latvijoje „Palink“ parduoda prekybos tinklą Latvijoje] ''Lithuanian''</ref><ref>[http://www.delfi.lv/bizness/uznemumi/mego-perk-iki-veikalu-tiklu-gaida-konkurences-uzraugu-atlauju.d?id=44046807 'Mego' pērk IKI veikalu tīklu; gaida konkurences uzraugu atļauju] ''Latvian''</ref>
The company currently operates over 240 "Iki", "Iki Cento" and "Iki Express" stores in more than 70 cities and is the second largest retail grocer in Lithuania.<ref>http://www.15min.lt/naujiena/verslas/bendroves/iki-i-tinklo-pletra-pernai-investavo-80-mln-lt-663-398501#ixzz2qVODXf4m</ref>
