{{Coord|47|08|24.00|N|9|31|27.90|E|display=title}} {{Infobox museum | name = Postal Museum | native_name = Postmuseum | native_name_lang = de | logo = | logo_upright = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | image = Engländerbau.jpg | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | map_type = | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord}} --> | former_name = | established = 1936 | dissolved = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | location = [[Vaduz]], [[Liechtenstein]] | type = [[Postal museum]] | accreditation = | key_holdings = | collections = | collection_size = | visitors = | founder = | executive_director = | leader_type = | leader = | director = | president = | ceo = | chairperson = | curator = | architect = | historian = | owner = | publictransit = | car_park = | parking = | network = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | embedded = }}
The '''Postal Museum''' ([[German language|German]]: ''Postmuseum'') is a [[postal museum]] in [[Vaduz]], [[Liechtenstein]]. It is a branch museum of [[Liechtenstein National Museum]].<ref name="tourismus.li">{{cite web|url=https://tourismus.li/en/lie/place/Postage+Stamp+Museum/|title=Postage Stamp Museum|website=tourismus.li}}</ref>
==History== The museum was founded in 1930 and opened in 1936.<ref name="tourismus.li"/> Afterwards, the museum had been relocated several times until it sits at its current building at English Building Art Space.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.landesmuseum.li/Default.aspx?tabid=79|title=Liechtenstein National Museum > Postal Museum|first=Liechtenstein National|last=Museum|website=www.landesmuseum.li}}</ref>
==Exhibitions== The museum exhibits postage stamps issued by Liechtenstein since 1912 and also the history of postal service of the country.<ref name="tourismus.li"/>
==See also== * [[Kunstmuseum Liechtenstein]]
