{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Use Singapore English|date=April 2018}} {{pp-semi-indef}} {{Infobox Network | network_name = Radio Corporation of Singapore | network_type = Public | genre = | available = Singapore | foundation = 1 October 1994 | dissolved = 12 February 2001 | location_city = [[Caldecott Hill|Caldecott Broadcast Centre]], [[Caldecott Hill]] | location_country = [[Singapore]] | broadcast_area = Singapore | airdate = 1 October 1994 | launch_date = 1 October 1994 | country = Singapore | locations = | industry = [[Broadcasting]] | groups = [[Radio]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | parent = Singapore International Media | website = [http://www.mediacorp.sg www.rcs.sg] | footnotes = | intl = }} The '''Radio Corporation of Singapore''' was a Singaporean radio broadcasting service. It was founded on 1 October 1994 and dissolved on 11 February 2001. It was one of the autonomous branches of the [[Singapore Broadcasting Corporation]].
