The '''Salale Oromo people''' (also Selale) are an [[Oromo people|Oromo]] subgroup inhabiting the northern [[Shewa]] region of [[Ethiopia]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=fg1zCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA128|title=The Oromo and the Christian Kingdom of Ethiopia: 1300-1700|last=Hassen|first=Mohammed|date=2015|publisher=Boydell & Brewer|year=|isbn=9781847011176|location=|pages=128|language=en}}</ref> They have a population of approximately 2 million.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=54gyRnhIugkC&pg=PA205&dq=salale+oromo&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjxjr-m5vDUAhXoLsAKHeo-C8sQ6AEIRDAF#v=onepage&q=salale%20oromo&f=false|title=Peoples on the Move: Introducing the Nomads of the World|last=Phillips|first=David J.|date=2001|publisher=William Carey Library|year=|isbn=9780878083527|location=|pages=205|language=en}}</ref>
== See also == * [[List of Oromo subgroups and clans]]
